name: Pura Luhur Tamba Waras
address: Sangketan, Penebel, Tabanan Regency, Bali 82152, Indonesia

There are lot of herbal plantation, also good vegetation to help maintain our health. The priest or we call Mangku of Hindu who lead the pray, blessing, also can share the benefit of some plantation for health & hindu ceremony usage that found at the Pura. The Mangku Gede is also teacher. Thank you, stay happy & healthy. Namaste üôè
review 2: Great place for  nature photigraphy entusiast. Very clean and cold. You can pray and doing "melukat" here. For who want to having melukat, you have to bring 2 pcs of balinese coconut. You will get a black and white rope bracelet.
review 3: A place for Balinese to ask blessings & cureness for any known sickness. It is believed as a place where "a higher divine doctor" can cure those who ask for it-- body and soul.. üôèüòáüòá
review 4: Famous in tabanan for its healing properties, in fact the name itself ( Tambo Waras / Excellent Medication ) already decribe this place for you. In a nutshell this place serve locals a place to heal themselves without drugs, as for effective or not is not clear as local superstition and religion has rooted deep in this place. For tourist vosotong this place is not recommended as it was far from nearby town, and other tourist attraction making it less favorable. Instead you can just go to Tirta Empul.
review 5:
Luhur Tamba Waras Temple

(Place for Inner Birth Health Request)

Luhur Tamba Waras Temple is geographically located on the southern slope of Mount Batukaru, precisely in Sangketan Village, Penebel, Tabanan.  The temple is on one line with Luhur Temple Batukaru is located at an altitude of about 725 meters above sea level.  To reach this temple pemedek must cover a distance of about 22 km from the city of Tabanan.  If seen from the temple structure, Pura Luhur Tamba Waras or also called Tambo Waras is located as a pharmacy warehouse in the universe.  This function can be proven by the emergence of various important facilities that function as medicinal ingredients, in addition to being closely related to history, where a king can be cured by arranging requests in a place that was originally a wilderness of Batukaru.
